    "Dataset ConstructionData Sources.",
    "Our urban planning textual data collection primarily focuses on two key sources: urban planning textbooks and past urban planning exams, with the overview of the dataset's statistics shown in Table 3.",
    "Urban planning textbooks encompass a wide spectrum of general knowledge about urban planning, thus leveraging data from textbooks enables LLMs to establish a foundational understanding of the specific domain, mirroring the approach taken by human planners who frequently refer to textbooks as their primary learning and training resources.In addition, questions found in urban planning exams adhere to specific formats and emphasize particular areas.",
    "Therefore, finetuning LLMs with data extracted from real exams serves to further refine their abilities, enhancing their accuracy in addressing domainspecific exam questions.",
    "Particularly, as the introduced benchmark UrbanPlanBench is sourced from the latest publicly available urban planning exam in China held in 2022, we utilize exam questions predating 2022 for the collection of SFT data, spanning eight years."
  ],
